{"questionId":"3306677","questionHtml":"<p>Determine an equation for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to set up a direct variation equation that includes a constant, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>, or the calculation of a constant using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g., <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> <strong>OR</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>50</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00492</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>203</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>252</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00492</mn><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>203</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3306677","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ1.6a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Determine an equation for d in terms of v.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvaila